cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with pre-trained word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a systematic approach for selecting the best embeddings for a downstream task, which involves evaluation and visualization, indicating that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. The paper also mentions the use of word analogy lists, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks. Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to named entity recognition (NER), which is a subfield of natural language processing, and neural engineering (cs.NE) could also be a relevant subcategory.
